  6  The real numbers ℝ.
  7  
  8  They are constructed as the topological completion of ℚ. With the following steps:
  9  (1) prove that ℚ forms a uniform space.
 10  (2) subtraction and addition are uniform continuous functions in this space
 11  (3) for multiplication and inverse this only holds on bounded subsets
 12  (4) ℝ is defined as separated Cauchy filters over ℚ (the separation requires a quotient construction)
 13  (5) extend the uniform continuous functions along the completion
 14  (6) proof field properties using the principle of extension of identities
 15
